# --- IndianLegal-LLM ignores ---
# Corpora and models never live in the repo (CLAUDE.md §5: process in the cloud,
# only code/configs go up, only a 50-200MB adapter comes down).
# data/* (not data/) so git still descends and the golden-eval negations below
# can take effect (a wholesale `data/` exclusion can't be re-included into).
data/*
# ...but DO version-control the small, hand-curated golden EVAL set: the seed
# queries and the human-verified citations are eval ground truth (config, not a
# corpus). The generated review artifact (golden_candidates.jsonl) stays ignored.
!data/eval/
data/eval/*
!data/eval/golden_queries.yaml
!data/eval/golden.jsonl
models/
adapters/
outputs/
*.safetensors
*.gguf
*.bin
*.pt
*.ckpt

# Secrets / local config
.env
.env.local

# Python
__pycache__/
*.py[cod]
*$py.class
*.egg-info/
.eggs/
build/
dist/
.installed.cfg
*.egg

# Virtual environments
.venv/
venv/
env/
ENV/

# Eval gate artifacts (written by CI / local runs; never committed)
eval_metrics.json
eval_summary.md

# Build/data-collection logs
*.log

# Tooling caches
.pytest_cache/
.mypy_cache/
.ruff_cache/
.coverage
htmlcov/
.tox/

# Notebooks / cloud scratch
.ipynb_checkpoints/

# Editors / OS
.idea/
.vscode/
*.swp
.DS_Store
Thumbs.db
